OL,3,CVictims sidelined in new 'outrageous'
OL,4,CBill, says Barnaby Webber's mother
OL,6,FShe warns that it could strip bereaved
OL,7,Ffamilies of the right to be consulted
OL,8,For informed about major decisions
OL,9,Frelating to mentally disordered
OL,10,Foffenders.
OL,12,FThe Victims and Courts Bill will give
OL,13,Fvictims no statutory right to be told
OL,14,Fabout decisions affecting the
OL,15,Fdetention, leave or discharge of their
OL,16,Foffenders with its current provisions,
OL,17,Faccording to national charity Hundred
OL,18,FFamilies.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/11
