OL,4,CBill, says Barnaby Webber's mother
OL,6,FShe described the provisions as "a
OL,7,Fdevastating oversight that repeats the
OL,8,Fvery failings we are now reliving
OL,9,Fthrough the public inquiry".
OL,11,FMs Webber added: "This Bill, if passed
OL,12,Fin its current form, will entrench a
OL,13,Fsystem that sidelines victims of the
OL,14,Fmost serious mental health-related
OL,15,Fkillings.
OL,17,F"It cannot be allowed to proceed
OL,18,Funnoticed and unchallenged.
