OL,6,F"Our lives are shattered; our trauma
OL,7,Fdeeper than you could possibly
OL,8,Fimagine, but yet again, a new fight
OL,9,Fhas seemingly been thrown at us."
OL,11,FThe moment Calocane was arrested by
OL,12,Fpolice
OL,14,FCampaigners have called on victims
OL,15,Fminister Alex Davies-Jones to amend
OL,16,Fthe Bill by guaranteeing all victims
OL,17,Fhave the right to be consulted,
OL,18,Freceive necessary information and be
OL,19,Finformed of key decisions, and to
OL,20,Fcreate a formal appeal process when
OL,21,Finformation is denied.
