OL,3,CVictims sidelined in new 'outrageous'
OL,4,CBill, says Barnaby Webber's mother
OL,6,F"This is not about punishment. It's
OL,7,Fabout basic fairness, compassion, and
OL,8,Ftransparency. Victims and their
OL,9,Ffamilies should not be shut out of
OL,10,Fdecisions that affect their personal
OL,11,Fsafety and recovery.
OL,13,F"We have a lamentably long track
OL,14,Frecord in our country of ignoring
OL,15,Fvictims of serious crime. That has to
OL,16,Fstop. There is a balance to be struck.
OL,18,F"The Government has a clear
OL,19,Fopportunity to put this right and they
OL,20,Fmust not waste it."
